 offices where ecologists regulate the use of genetically modified organisms, to remote islands where conservationists eradicate invasive species, Wanderer explores how scientific research informs, and is informed by, concepts of nation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aBiopoliticszMexico. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  aaxolotl.  abiodiversity.  abiology.  abiopolitics.  abiosecurity.  abuen vivir.  aconservation.  aecology.  aecosystem.  aenvironment.  aenvironmentalism.  ageci.  agoats.  aguadalupe.  aimmunology.  ainvasive species.  aland management.  alatin america.  amexico.  amice.  amicrobes.  amicrobiology.  anative species.  anature.  anonfiction.  anonhuman animals.  apollution.  asalamander.  ascience.  avirus.  avivir bien.  avivir mejor.  awhalers.  awildlife.  azoology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520972537zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520972537423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520972537.jpg  a978-3-11-069041-5  UC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyt